{"/service/ndnp/curiv/batch_curiv_llano_ver01/data/sn85066387/00175047876/1908051701/0412.xml":{"full_text":"VOLUME CIIL\u2014 NO. 169. FIRST NEWS SECTION\nPROSPERITY ON\nITS WAY BACK,\nSAYS HARRIMAN\nDeclares Business Outlook Is\nExcellent and Crops\nAll Good\nSays There Has Been Too Much\nUnrest Among the Whole\nPeople\nAsserts He Is Out of Politics.\nbat Will Spend Money\nHis Own Way\nSPECIAL DISPATCH TO THE CALL\nWASHINGTON, May 16.\u2014 E. H.\nHarriman left this afternoon for New\nYork. He paid no calls on public offi\ncials, but declared that prosperity was\non its way back and would get here\njust about in proportion as the people\nreturned to sound, sensible under\nstanding of business conditions.\n**The feeling is easier, and all the\ncountry needs now is to be let alone.\nThere has been altogether too much\nunrest I don't mean on the part of\nanybody in particular, but among the\nwhole people.\n\"The business outlook is excellent.\nThere has not been a spring In many\nyears when the prospect for crops was\nbetter than now. Everything else de\npends on agriculture.\"\n\"And about politics, Mr. Harrtman?\"\n\"Oh, I'm I was going to say I'm out\nof that. But I really never rai In It. i\nI don't know anything about politics\nand I don't expect to.\"\"\n\"Don't expect to finance any cam\nlaign this year, then?\"\n\"Oh. now, I never did that net real\nly, you know. I claim the right to\nuse my own In my own way. I have\nthat right.\"\nMELBA WOULD SING\nWITH MME. TETIfcAZZIM\nSong Bird Has Not Yet Heard\nNew Favorite, but Looks\nForward to Pleasure\nSPECIAL CABLE TO THE CALJ,\nLONDON. May 16.\u2014 Melba arrived\nfrom Paris today and was asked by\nThe Call's correspondent:\n\"Is it true that you are to appear\nv,:ih Tetratzlni next season?\"\n\"As yet I have heard nothing of such\na possibility, but there are several\noperas that would admit of It. the\n'Marriage of Figaro' and 'Don Glovonnl.'\nfor example.\n\"I would enter heartily Into such a\nproposal. I have on various occasions\nsung In 'Michaela.' Margaret of Va\nlois\" and 'The Infanta* in order to make\nit possible for an unusual cast, such\nas Mmes. Pattl. Nielson. Tietjens and\nrayself to appear together. What was\npossible then should be easily possible\n\"I have never heard Tetrazzlni, nor\nhave I met her. but I intend to enjoy\nthat double pleasure at the earliest op\nportunity.\" was the smiling reply. \"I\nhave not had much opportunity for\nhearing other artists. During the opera\nseason I am a very busy woman. When\nI was aty.he Manhattan Beason before\nlast I was able to vl^it the theater and\nhear Calve and Donalda but twice in all\nthat time. I visited the Metropolitan\nonce and heard 'Parsifal.*\nPLAN ADJOURNMENT OF\nCONGRESS ON THURSDAY\nRepublican Leaders Propose the\nPassage of Currency Bill\nto End Session\nSPECIAL DISPATCH TO THE CALL\nWASHINGTON. May 16.\u2014 A tentative\nagreement to adjourn Thursday next at\nmidnight has been reached by the house\nand 6enate republican leaders.- The plan\nhinges on currency legislation and the\n\\u25a0position to be taken by the democrats\nof the senate.\nIf the democrats decide to let the re\npublicans pass their currency bill and\ntake the responsibility for the legisla-'\ntien a vote will be had in the senate\nnext Tuesday and adjournment will\nfollow Thursday.\nThe bouse leaders are no* working\non the plan of Thursday night ad\njournment, and bills desired by repub\nlican members who h,ave influence with\nthe speaker are being rushed through.\nSAN JOSE GIRL SECURES\nARTS DEGREE AT VASSAR\nMiss Martha Love Williams\nRepresents Pacific Coast\nin Graduating Class\nSPECIAL DISPATCH TO UHE CALL\nPOUGHKEEPSIE, May 16.\u2014 Amoris\nthe girls who will receive the bachelor\nof arts degree with honors at Vassar\ncollege commencement, June a, is Miss\nMartha Love Williams of San Jose, Cal.\nShe Is the only girl In the graduating\nclass from the Pacific coast\nThe San Francisco Call.\nINDEX OF THE\nSAN FRANCISCO CALL